Peel the @cucumber{1} and the @carrot{6%ounce}. Using a #vegetable peeler{}, shave the carrot and cucumber into ribbons lengthwise. Discard the inner cores. Peel and mince the @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate.

== Quick Pickled Veggie Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @green cabbage{4%ounce}, cucumber, carrot, @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a @salt{large pinch}. Set aside to marinate. The longer it sits, the better!

== Dumpling Filling ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @ground pork{8%ounce}, ginger, garlic, scallion whites, and @soy sauce{1%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembling and Cooking Dumplings ==

Fill a #small bowl{} with water and keep it to the side. Place a @wonton wrappers{1} on a dry and clean surface and fill it with a teaspoonful of dumpling filling. With your fingertips, moisten the edges of one half of the wrapper, fold over the other half, and press to seal. Set aside under a damp #towel{} and repeat.

Heat a thin layer of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, cook the dumplings for about ~{1%minute} per side, until golden brown. Set aside and repeat. Once all the dumplings are seared, return them to the pan. Reduce the heat to low and carefully pour @water{1/4%cup} into the pan. Cover and cook gently for ~{8-10%minutes}. Uncover and cook over medium-high heat for ~{2%minutes} more, until the water evaporates.

== Dipping Sauce ==

While the dumplings cook, combine the remaining @soy sauce{6.5%teaspoon} with @sugar{1%tablespoon} and the scallion greens.

Serve the dumplings with the quick pickled veggie salad and the dipping sauce. Enjoy!